    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <description>Tutanota is the world's most secure email service, easy to use and private by design. Sign up for free encrypted email now.

With end-to-end encryption and 2FA, your emails have never been more secure. The built-in encryption guarantees that your mailbox belongs to you: Nobody can decrypt or read your data.

**Please Note**: This is an automatically updated package. If you find it is out of date by more than a day or two, please contact the maintainer(s) and let them know the package is no longer updating correctly.</description>
    <summary>Tutanota is an email client with a strong focus on security and privacy that lets you encrypt emails on all your devices.</summary>
    <releaseNotes>
# What's new
 - EditAll non-reschedule operations propagate to altered instances [#10389](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10389)
 - Memory leaks when resizing the client [#10050](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10050)
 - Update Calendar Service to handle default calendars [#10018](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10018)
 - Add policy to avoid flooding calendar with pending invitaitons E.g: Display only invites from Tuta contacts [#9765](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/9765)
 - Unacknowledged events as ghost bubbles [#5755](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/5755)
 - Same contacts can be imported multiple times [#3707](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/3707)

# Bugfixes
 - Fix electron deprecations and keyboard navigaiton shortcut [#10357](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10357)
 - All day altered instances become normal events when there is any update to the original series [#10344](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10344)
 - Fix bugs with outdated cache after key rotation [#10321](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10321)
 - Text Labels are not read by screen readers [#10274](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10274)
 - Handle exclusions when turn normal series into all-day series [#10261](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10261)
 - Process new all-day Altered Instance [#10260](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10260)
 - sent emails are duplicated into draft [#10220](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10220)
 - Attachment names are not displayed when printing email [#10218](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10218)
 - Crypto error when decrypting contact fields with a cardinality of ZeroOrOne and an empty value [#10204](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10204)
 - The mail editor doesn't fallback to default sender when the sender alias is deactivated while the editor is open or minimized [#10186](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10186)
 - Accepted events can be edited on guest's calendar by dragging and dropping, but this should not be possible [#10177](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10177)
 - AssertNotNull failed : You can't get server time if no rest requests were made [#10176](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10176)
 - Cannot unassign label from mail when: mailbox labels count &gt; MAX_NBR_OF_MAILS_SYNC_OPERATION [#10166](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10166)
 - Cannot download uploaded attachment from the mail editor [#10120](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10120)
 - Reply is not filling the recipient address in To field automatically [#10016](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10016)
 - Aliases form is not updated after upgrade [#2464](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/2464)

